00:00:57,788 --> 00:01:02,531
I will try to give you a feel of the arcade industry, because most of you were not around

22
00:01:02,531 --> 00:01:05,412
in the early 1980s to 1985 to really know what it was like.

23
00:01:05,412 --> 00:01:09,814
And I also want to preface this by saying it's been 26 years since I've worked on Gauntlet,

24
00:01:09,814 --> 00:01:12,836
so I've forgotten a lot of things.

25
00:01:12,836 --> 00:01:17,998
And more so than that, when I left Atari, I left all my notes behind, so I had a hard

